"If you could go back and change any one thing to make everything better, and risk screwing everything in your life up, would you?"
Saw that in an away message earlier today and it got me thinking. I started trying to think of anything in my past that was worth the risk. After a good couple of hours I still hadn't even come up with anything significant I wanted to change in my past at all. Sure there were plenty of little things I would change, like saying something that I didn't, holding my tongue when I should have or starting my homework more in advance. But when it comes down to it, none of that really matters. Anything that I might consider changing wouldn't really change anything, and the more I think about it I think I like it that way. The more I think about my life, the more I realize that there isn't anything I want to change about my life. My childhood was good (even though I didn't have too many friends I preferred it that way, honestly). High school was awesome, had all the friends I wanted (all 3 of them), I enjoyed learning, teachers were nice, classes were interesting, life was good. It might have been nice to have a better GPA or SAT score, but I still got into my first choice school, so they didn't really matter. College is good, I'm enjoying what I'm learning, getting involved in activities that I don't have the time for, having a great time overall. Love life is just where I want it... nonexistent (like I have time for that right now), but I have had enough experience with love to know what I am missing and like it that way. So long entry made short, I really can't think of anything I would change in my past, whether it might screw everything up or work out perfectly. In my opinion there's nothing to fix. Other than that, since I haven't posted in a while (ok a long while), the rest of summer went great, the co-op first session wrapped up perfectly with an exit interview/review which included "In his first session, Miles raised the bar for the level of expectation of Co-op performance. In my mind, all other Co-ops will be judged against Miles until an UberMiles comes forth.", a quote from one of my bosses. If you wanna read my official report of the co-op session its here(just cancel the security box if you get it). After getting back and finding out that my luggage had decided to take a side trip to Cancun (why didn't it just go to Tijuana while we were in San Diego?) my week at home went well. I worked a shift at Villa and got to see people from there, got to see Kevin ad Cari's new house and find out that their 5 year old son, Grant, can throw a football 10 times better than I could ever hope to (The kid can throw a 15 yard perfect spiral where it needs to go almost every time). Now I'm back at Purdue, pretty sure that I'm gonna major in structures now, with a minor maybe in propulsion. Classes for the semester are good, I'm in AAE 340 (rigid body dynamics), AAE 301 (signals and processing), AAE 333 (aerodynamics), AAE 352 (structures) and MATH 304 (differential equations 2) so its not too bad of a schedule, I just wish that the homework was spread out better and didn't all seem like it was due on wednesdays. I'm still in the LARP group over here, having lots of fun with that, and actually this semester I'm DMing too, so that should be interesting. Also starting this semester I joined the Kuk Sool club (a Korean martial arts) so in time I will know kung fu.... Now that I've wasted tons of space on ppl's friends page I think my mission is complete.

So here I am, at work again on a weekend...this next paycheck is gonna be awesome. Today's been the second day its since i've been out here, and the last time was even less than that. Some would probably thing that this is a good thing, but seeing Niki's journals is making me miss having a good downpour every now and then. Guess that's what i get for being in southern California. Speaking of California, tuesday there was an earthquake... just a 5.3 and only lasted for about 2 or 3 seconds, and it's epicenter was 50 miles WSW so it was pretty decently offshore, but that didn't stop me from having to stabilize my monitor so that I could work. On wednesday I decided to try making some chainmail so I convinced my roommate to take a 30 (should have been 15, I swear) minute drive to Lowes to pick up some wire, plyers, dowel rods, and tin snips. I've already got about a square foot done and it seems to be turning out rathar nicely, but now I need to get more wire (hiroomiehowareyoudoingtodayisthereanythingIcandoforyou) because I've just about used it all up. Though I did find a site where I could order it for about $.90/lb rather than the $2.38/lb the stuff I got in the store comes out to, being the engineer I am I decided to write a couple of algebraic functions for each type of wire (can't forget to include the $10 for the first pound + $.60/lb thereafter for shipping from Canadia) and see what poundage they intersect at (cuz I'm estimating that I'll need about 15 lbs of wire). Now that I've talked enough about nothing important at all I think I shall leave you with the fact that they intersect at about 10.7lbs looks like I have some online shopping to do. Almost forgot to mention that I tried surfing (I'm shocked too) last sunday. All I can say is that I have a lot more respect for mother nature/the ocean, I was beat after just paddling out for the first time.

Ten thirty on a friday night and where is Miles? Sitting at his computer in his cubicle updating his journal while he "makes his presence be known" at the office during the construction, where else would I be. As I'm looking at my time sheet I'm noticing a big trend over the past four weeks that I've been here... 10.75 project hours (the actual work) 42.25 training hours (to be expected) 120 facility hours (moving crap around during their remodeling) hmmmmm, so I haven't been really doing all that much engineering work but at least after next week I think I can honestly say that either the other co-op or I have moved every book, chair, white and cork board, desk, bookshelf etc in this office. So if we have moved everything then by my reasoning there is nothing left to move.... and that leaves me with what... that glorious thing called time. Time to do all this project work people keep telling me they have for me to do as soon as I have the time. On another note, I took some pics a couple weekends ago when I went to the beach, thought I'd share a few, just to show how horrible the weather is out here
sorry about the un-horizontal horizon on the second one, I would have fixed it but to keep it square it would have involved cutting off too much of the edges for my liking

Your dominant hues are cyan and green. Although you definately strive to be logical you care about people and know there's a time and place for thinking emotionally. Your head rules most things but your heart rules others, and getting them to meet in the middle takes a lot of your energy some days.

Your saturation level is medium - You're not the most decisive go-getter, but you can get a job done when it's required of you. You probably don't think the world can change for you and don't want to spend too much effort trying to force it.

Your outlook on life is very bright. You are sunny and optimistic about life and others find it very encouraging, but remember to tone it down if you sense irritation.

gen eds are supposed to lighten up your load and make it easier, or at elast thats what my advisor tells me...I just think there annoying, pointless and do nothing that remotely resembles making your load easier, I'm here for a degree in engineering, not liberal arts.  I don't care if I'm a rounded individual, that's up to me to decide, not the college.  if I want to be fucked by putting all my eggs in a very tiny basket then I should be allowed to, arent I the one paying them to educate me, shouldn't I decide what I want to learn

on a side not i got a fortune cookie that said "you will finish your project ahead of schedule" ... just thought that was kinda funny

You are Form 9, Vampire: The Undying. "And The Vampire was all that remained on
the blood drowned creation. She attempted to
regrow life from the dead. But as she was
about to give the breath of life, she was
consumed in the flame of The Phoenix and the
cycle began again." Some examples of the Vampire Form are Hades (Greek)
and Isis (Egyptian). The Vampire is associated with the concept of
death, the number 9, and the element of fire. Her sign is the eclipsed moon. As a member of Form 9, you are a very realistic
individual. You may be a little idealistic,
but you are very grounded and down to earth.
You realize that not everything lasts, but you
savor every minute of the good times. While
you may sometimes find yourself lonely, you
have strong ties with people that will never be
broken. Vampires are the best friends to have
because they are sensible.

finally got a break this weekend, really needed it too, after almost 8 weeks of straight classes I needed a couple days off, the only thing that sux about it is that we jump back into classes on a Wednesday, and lucky for me everything is due on wednesdays.  

it was nice to be home for a couple of days though even though I wasn't home much (worked a 5-close sat, open-close sun and 5-semi close mon) but the money was well worth it.  plus I was able to steal one of the big trays to make a shield out of.  also picked up another studded belt so I can finish my leg armor, and now that I have everything I need I should be able to finish all the armor soon, assuming I can stand sewing all the plates into the brigandine.

now if I could only have gotten some sleep last night instead of doing homework

so the weekend was nice, now that its Tuesday and all I can look back at it and wish I was there again.  played random board games with a little bit of the original nes version of pictionary thrown in on Friday night.  larped all Saturday day (and I actually managed to hold my own and take well more than my share in the line battles, even got spike with the greatsword a few times) but then dnd'd all sat night.  that appeased the nerd gods enough for then so I decided to catch up on some homework on Sunday, but still, at that point nothing could break my spirits, well other than Monday, but that was still a day away so what did I care.  

on Monday I got my thermo exam back, beat the average by 3 points, so at least I'm somewhat ahead of the game (for now)  also gave my first speech for the year in debate and that seemed to go more than well.  after that I preddymuch sat on my ass and did nothing,  wish I could still be doing that now, but now its homework time!!!

I'm starting to wonder if its a problem that I'm becoming bored with many of my classes already.  I just sit there and stare at my pencil knowing I should be writing but not.  this really didn't happen last year, and I can't really say I ever remember it really being a factor in high school, there was always some little bit of enthusiasm in me that really wanted to learn the material (I always knew I was a nerd).  now I just cant wait for the class to be over and for me to leave.  then again, I guess it is a good sign that I continue to attend. anyways, now I'm off to my second exam of the week, yeay for linear algebra

there are so many days that I double click the lj icon and stare at the blank box trying to think of something that I could write down, something that at least seemed semi-worthy of putting in my journal.  in the end I just delete the three words I have, click the little red x and go on with doing whatever it was that I was doing before I clicked the lj icon, unfortunately that usually is looking for something to do, which is probably the heart of the problem, in that I spend so much time looking for something to do or deciding what I want to do that in he end nothing happens, and thus, have nothing to write about.  therefore (getting to the point of this entry) I have decided that in order to motivate myself to do more, I am going to write more, no matter what it is, because if I have nothing to write it will at least make me have a low enough self esteem that I will do something to make myself feel better.  so, in essence, this is a pre-offense apology to all for the meaningless crap that will be posted in the future (and at present as I look up)

so I kinda just forgot all about this thing all summer, not like there was really anything to write about over summer though, work, work, work more, sleep every now and then, relax every chance possible, and that's about it.

schools back now though, and that's turning out better than I thought, roommate worked out real well, oddly enough, mondays, wednesdays and fridays are kinda rough, but tuesdays and thursdays make up for them (6, 6, 5, 2, and 1 classes per day respectively) plus on tuesdays and thursdays I'll have plenty of time to catch up on all my work.

also I'm getting further and further with my armor for larp (I've already got 1/2 the steel plates sewn in and the studs I took from the belt look like they're gonna work perfectly), definitely looking forward to getting back into that.

now I've gotta get the motivation to go buy my books so I can actually do the homework due tomorrow.

might as well think of something to write in here, its the only think i haven't done yet to avoid studying for my finals next week, and since its the last week of classes everythings wrapping up so not much'll be due over the next couple of days.  who knows i might just pick up a book and read WHAT?!?! did i just say that, what a leap for miles, even thought i probably wont pick up the book,  at least i considered it as an option, and that's a big step for me.  so, other than my new affinity to books not much is new.  my awesome aunt chrys sent me more mcdonalds dollars....mmmmmm, i've got $15 that's alota good eatin.  
got my tooth fixed, at least i wont be cutting my tongue anymore, and even though i had tons of hmwk that weekend i still hung out with ann and cherie, but when do i ever do homework when i have a good excuse to avoid it.  also found out that i'm apparently going to desales' prom...so i also got a tux rented.  its definitely going to be...interesting, 
as for now, all the big projects of the semester are done, now its just a waiting game till the finals are over and i get to go home and find a day job to complement working at the villa

yeah, so today really sucks
first i can barely sleep in from all the construction going on rigt outside my window
then i get to my chem lab and realise i forgot the lab report from last week, so i run back to the dorm and print it off and go sprinting out the door, unfortunatley my head was slightly infront of my body when i got to the door and i just barely hit it on the window (at least i think i did, it was really so soft i could barely feel it, butanyways, for some reason when i opened the door my tooth decided to break off yet again, making it a overall count of 5 (1st grade, 6th grade, 8th grade 2x, and now)
but wait, it gets better, because i dont know when i'm gonna be able to get somewhere to get this fixed, so not only do i have an oversensitive front tooth in the shape of a foam finger (well with a short finger) but i get to deal with it for who knows how long
plus the damn thing is semi-sharp, so if i move my lip in the wrong way i get a nice big gash through it
and now i get to go and find out that i failed a math exam

I dont know why I dont write much in this anymore, its not like I cant make the time (though that is an excuse I use for myself).  maybe I just never have anything to say, like right now, i'm not even really saying anything.  maybe I just dont have an interesting enough life and need to find something worth writing down.  that's doubtful though.  honestly its probably the fact that I am still trying to figure out what I like and dont in this world and once I find it then I will have something to say about both of them, what I like and what I dont.  you'd think that by now in my life I might know what I like, but what can I say, i've always been a bit slower than people doing things, that way I know I did them myself and did them the best that I could, I mean why should I do something if I am not going to get everything out of it that I can, why should I bother with something I dont like, but who knows how much time i'm wasting thinking about stuff rather than just trying it.  

i'll figure it out...in time

finally back here at school, ready to get this sesmeter over with.  stilll waiting to hear from the guy about my co-op.  hes narrowed it down to nine and i'm still in it, but thats still only a one in nine chance, so i'm still keepin my fingers crossed, why is that supposed to help anyway, what good will crossing your fingers do except make it really hard to type, as if i dont already have enough problems with that.  i need to hear from him soon though, i need ot know if i should schedule classes for next semester or for the summer.

other than that i had a good spring break, went to SC and saw the grandparents aunts and cousins (uncles were busy).  rained every day we were there though and in columbus the weather was perfect...just my luck

hmmm...been awhile so maybe i'll do a life update....seems like i never write in this anymore.

so....umm.... where to start....hmmmm...

<lj-cut text="blah blah blah">
lets start with the now.
spring break is in just one more day!! and of course all my morning classes get canceled, but none of my afternoon's do so i'm stuck here till 5:30, but thats ok i guess, i like being here anyway.
"whats that you say?? you like being here" " why yes, i actually do" i love it here.  you would think that i get lonely because my closest friends here are mere acquaintances that i say hi to in passing on the streets, yet it doesnt seem to matter to me.  i know i'm always complaining about all of my classes, but i actually love all of them, even chem.  this might sound arrogant but this is the first time i have really been academically challenged and for once i feel like i'm learning... and i'm loving every minute of it...the late nights studying, the extreme amount of work just to get one stupid assignment done, the boring lectures that i attend anyway, i really cant complain about any of it.  i truly feel like i'm learning something for once in my life.

got a chem midterm in ten minutes and here i am sitting and typing on lj for the first time in weeks, what a time to pick, o well, my philosophy is that if i dont know it by now i wont, so i might as well relax and not worry about it until its staring me in the face, but stick around and you'll probably find out how i think i did, cuz this probably wont be done before i head out.

i joined my first campus organization, its called champions grove LARP, and for all the people who actually know what larp is and care enough to read this far all i have to say is "what...its fun" for those who dont know what it is well i'll tell you
basically larp is live action role playing, basically like acting, but this group is kinda a different larp cuz were larping dnd which is ... yeah... larp+hack 'n slash = make swords out of pvc, fun noodles, duct tape and tube socks and beat each other with them... what its fun...really  plus i always wanted to learn how to sword fight, and this gives me a lot of every world, there are fencing ppl in it, so i am learnin some of that, then there are the ppl who have done this for a long time and can teach you about anything about using a long sword of bastard sword, so its a beat ppl learning experience.
what can i say we all know i'm a dork.

hmm, chem test now, i'll be back to finish later.......................
eh, harder than i thought, but thats what i expected, if that makes any sense

anyways, despite the fact that spring break is coming up i might not be spending too much time at home.  probably going to SC to visit the grandparents (and no, they're not at the beach, in fact they're about as far from the beach as you can get). but it looks like i might be there from monday to thursday, and its supposed to be raining and high 60's all week long there....what fun, what fun,
